So what really happend on the bridge?
 During one of PewDiePie's live streams. PewDiePie was playing a video game, and in frustration, he used a racial slur. The specific word he used was a racial slur commonly directed at people of African descent. The incident sparked immediate controversy and criticism.

PewDiePie later issued an apology on his YouTube channel, acknowledging the inappropriateness of his language and expressing regret for using such a derogatory term. He stated that he was not trying to justify his words and that he understood the impact of his actions.

This incident had consequences for PewDiePie's business relationships. Following the controversy, the developers of the game he was playing, Firewatch, requested that he not play or stream their games in the future. Additionally, he faced criticism from various media outlets and the broader online community.

It's worth noting that this incident was part of a series of controversies surrounding PewDiePie during that time, including the aforementioned anti-Semitic content controversy. While he maintained a massive following, these incidents prompted discussions about responsibility and accountability among content creators on platforms like YouTube.

While in the process of trying to repair things with my father, he fell victim to suicide in December of 2020. I saw him for thanksgiving and he was gone a week later. He had battled Hodgkin‚Äôs lymphoma twice. The second time took such an intense toll on his mental health, and after remission he convinced himself that he would not be able to go through another year of treatment if was to return a 3rd time.

Fast forward to 2023, we have a babygirl, 2 dogs a house, both of us are very health and living our best life. So to all of you fighters out there, as long as there is life, there is hope, keep fighting.
